Description: Fragment of oval handle, rising to sharp turn, of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine buff-brown; dark inclusions; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Aristratos. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 25, 2. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 266.39.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1143)
